                    They passed a constitution and by-laws and accepted the resignations of Mrs. L.
                    Brotherton and Mr. William C. Eyster on account of their relocation to Virginia.
                    The association plans to erect a monument in memory of Franklin's dead soldiers.
                    It now has between $800 and $900 and expects $1400 in the next several months.</summary>
